1. Clone the whole repo into your either Git or Github desktop ( I use desktop Github app and it looks easy after some tries)

2. Before you start making any changes or just viewing, always fetch original to get the latest updated version from the team!!!

3. use your Laptop Powershell ( for windows )

4. Type in this line: cd WhereYouStoreTheProject\NameOfRepo\backend e.g. cd "D:\Onedrive\Documents\GitHub\EatWellthy\backend"
   node --watch server

5. Open another Powershell window and
   Type in this line: cd WhereYouStoreTheProject\NameOfRepo\frontend e.g. cd "D:\Onedrive\Documents\GitHub\EatWellthy\client"
   $env:NODE_OPTIONS="--openssl-legacy-provider" Only if you node.js version is >= V17
   npm run start

6. The web app window should pop out from your default browser
